snippet.textDisplay:
To everyone yelling: "The price is too crazy!" etc... How bout this > Buying a 1300 dollar DSLR camera with a nice zoom lens if you wanna take really good pictures, is something nobody will frown upon, right?? Or buying a decent $1300 laptop if you need a fast device to work on every day is also something most people will see as justifiable.
This S20 Ultra has BOTH of that. Incredible camera and super smooth performance, on a device you will probably use EVERY DAY.
So tell me... how is it not okay to pay that for a phone, but totally reasonable to pay that for a camera or laptop? 🤔
